HEADWORD: Post-disseizor
<hw>Post`-dis*sei"zor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>post-</ets> + <ets>disseizor</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld>
<def>A person who disseizes another of lands which the disseizee had
before recovered of the same disseizor.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

